<section class="fragment-plan" data-artifact="plan" data-slice="foundation" data-rev="0">
  <style>
    .fragment-plan { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }
    .fragment-plan .files-touched { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.85em; }
    .fragment-plan .files-touched th,
    .fragment-plan .files-touched td { text-align: left; padding: 0.4em 0.6em; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e7eb); }
    .fragment-plan .files-touched th { font-weight: 600; background: var(--color-surface-raised, #f9fafb); }
    .fragment-plan .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 0.15em 0.5em; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 0.75em; font-weight: 600; }
    .fragment-plan .badge-new { background: #d1fae5; color: #065f46; }
    .fragment-plan .badge-infra { background: #e0e7ff; color: #3730a3; }
    .fragment-plan .badge-config { background: #fef9c3; color: #713f12; }
    .fragment-plan .badge-domain { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
    .fragment-plan details.pl-row summary { cursor: pointer; list-style: none; }
    .fragment-plan details.pl-row summary::marker,
    .fragment-plan details.pl-row summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .fragment-plan details.pl-row summary::after { content: ' ▸'; font-size: 0.7em; color: var(--color-muted, #6b7280); }
    .fragment-plan details.pl-row[open] summary::after { content: ' ▾'; }
    .fragment-plan .pl-change { background: var(--color-surface-raised, #f9fafb); padding: 0.5em 0.8em; margin-top: 0.3em; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.82em; color: var(--color-text, #374151); }
    .fragment-plan .callout { padding: 0.75em 1em; border-radius: 6px; margin: 1em 0; font-size: 0.875em; }
    .fragment-plan .callout-risk { background: #fef2f2; border-left: 4px solid #ef4444; color: #7f1d1d; }
    .fragment-plan .callout-warn { background: #fffbeb; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; color: #78350f; }
    .fragment-plan .callout-info { background: #eff6ff; border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6; color: #1e3a5f; }
    .fragment-plan .callout strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.3em; }
    .fragment-plan details.pl-revs summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--color-muted, #6b7280); }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      .fragment-plan .files-touched th { background: #1f2937; }
      .fragment-plan .files-touched th, .fragment-plan .files-touched td { border-color: #374151; }
      .fragment-plan .pl-change { background: #1f2937; color: #d1d5db; }
      .fragment-plan .badge-new { background: #064e3b; color: #a7f3d0; }
      .fragment-plan .badge-infra { background: #1e1b4b; color: #a5b4fc; }
      .fragment-plan .badge-config { background: #422006; color: #fde68a; }
      .fragment-plan .badge-domain { background: #450a0a; color: #fca5a5; }
      .fragment-plan .callout-risk { background: #450a0a; color: #fca5a5; }
      .fragment-plan .callout-warn { background: #422006; color: #fde68a; }
      .fragment-plan .callout-info { background: #1e3a5f; color: #bfdbfe; }
    }
    :root[data-theme="light"] .fragment-plan .files-touched th { background: #f9fafb; }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .fragment-plan .files-touched th { background: #1f2937; }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .fragment-plan .files-touched th,
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .fragment-plan .files-touched td { border-color: #374151; }
    :root[data-theme="dark"] .fragment-plan .pl-change { background: #1f2937; color: #d1d5db; }
  </style>

  <table class="files-touched">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>File</th>
        <th>Status</th>
        <th>Module</th>
        <th>±LOC</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>.gitignore</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Standard Node/pnpm/Vite gitignore; excludes .env, wrangler local overrides, node_modules, dist.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>config</td><td>+30</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>.npmrc</code></summary><div class="pl-change">save-exact=true to enforce exact pinning; node-linker=hoisted for Windows path-length and Workers compat.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>toolchain</td><td>+4</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>package.json</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Exact-pinned deps: @tanstack/react-start (RC, no 1.167.68/.71 or 1.142.x), @cloudflare/vite-plugin, vitest, @playwright/test, typescript. Scripts: dev, build, typecheck, lint, test, test:e2e, audit.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>toolchain</td><td>+60</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>pnpm-lock.yaml</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Generated by pnpm install from exact-pinned package.json. Lockfile is the supply-chain gate.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>toolchain</td><td>generated</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>tsconfig.json</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Strict TypeScript; bundler module resolution; paths configured for app/ alias.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>config</td><td>+25</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app.config.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">TanStack Start app config with @cloudflare/vite-plugin; server preset: cloudflare-workers. NOT the deprecated Nitro preset.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>config</td><td>+20</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>wrangler.jsonc</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Cloudflare Workers config: name=waypoint, compatibility_date=2025-11-01, nodejs_compat flag, observability: {enabled: true} (observability bootstrap — routes all console.log to Logpush).</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>config</td><td>+25</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app/router.tsx</code></summary><div class="pl-change">TanStack Router createRouter() with TanStack Start integration; route tree from generated routeTree.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>scaffold</td><td>+15</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app/routes/__root.tsx</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Root route: HTML document shell, Outlet, head meta.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>scaffold</td><td>+30</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app/routes/index.tsx</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Placeholder index route: "Waypoint — coming soon" with page title. Replaced by design-system-shell slice.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>scaffold</td><td>+15</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app/client.tsx</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Client entry point: StartClient hydration.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>scaffold</td><td>+10</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>app/ssr.tsx</code></summary><div class="pl-change">SSR entry + Cloudflare Workers fetch handler: StartServer wrapping the router.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>scaffold</td><td>+10</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>vitest.config.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Vitest config: jsdom environment, React plugin, setupFiles, coverage provider v8.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>test</td><td>+20</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>vitest.setup.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">@testing-library/jest-dom matchers import; afterEach cleanup.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>test</td><td>+5</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>tests/smoke/app.test.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Vitest smoke: renders a minimal React component, asserts mount without crash. Proves the harness runs, not the app.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>test</td><td>+15</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>playwright.config.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Playwright config: baseURL=http://localhost:3000, webServer auto-starts pnpm dev, chromium project for CI speed.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>test</td><td>+25</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>tests/e2e/smoke.spec.ts</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Playwright smoke: navigate to /, assert page has visible content, assert zero uncaught console errors.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>test</td><td>+15</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>.github/workflows/ci.yml</code></summary><div class="pl-change">GitHub Actions: push+PR trigger; node 22; pnpm; install --frozen-lockfile; typecheck; vitest; playwright (chromium); pnpm audit; pin-check (no ^ or ~).</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>ci</td><td>+60</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>.env.example</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Documents three external prerequisites: Google/GitHub OAuth, OPENROUTER_API_KEY, BETTER_AUTH_SECRET, CLOUDFLARE creds. All commented with which slice each is needed by.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>docs</td><td>+20</td></tr>
      <tr><td><details class="pl-row"><summary><code>README.md</code></summary><div class="pl-change">Stub README: what Waypoint is, quick-start (pnpm install + pnpm dev), env var setup pointer, test commands, link to docs/.</div></details></td><td><span class="badge badge-new">new</span></td><td>docs</td><td>+40</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- Risk callouts -->
  <div class="callout callout-warn">
    <strong>@tanstack/cli create is alpha</strong>
    The scaffold CLI may produce stale output, miss the Cloudflare preset, or fail outright. Step 2 documents the manual fallback (compose Start scaffold from official docs). The scaffold output is audited for version pins regardless of origin.
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <strong>CI gate deferred until remote exists</strong>
    AC-F4 (CI gates on push) carries a proxy+deferral: the proxy is AC-F3 (local test harnesses pass), cleared by the first push to a GitHub remote. No remote exists yet, so this is planned and pre-registered, not silently dropped.
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <strong>Observability bootstrap included</strong>
    <code>wrangler.jsonc</code> seeds <code>observability: { enabled: true }</code> in this slice. All subsequent Worker log calls route to Cloudflare Logpush from their first deploy — the instrumentation plan's zero-cost signal layer requires no additional plumbing in later slices.
  </div>

  <details class="pl-revs">
    <summary>Prior revisions (0)</summary>
    <p style="font-size:0.82em;color:var(--color-muted,#6b7280);padding:0.5em 0">No prior revisions — initial plan.</p>
  </details>

  <script>
    (function () {
      var section = document.currentScript.closest('.fragment-plan');
      window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('sdlc:fragment-ready', {
        detail: {
          name: 'plan',
          artifact: 'plan',
          counts: { files: 20, modules: 5, risks: 3 }
        }
      }));
    })();
